Generates and verifies the "tool contracts" doc block (a bulleted summary of each CLI binary's `--contract` output) embedded in CLAUDE.md, template/CLAUDE.md, and README.md between `BEGIN GENERATED tool-contracts` / `END GENERATED tool-contracts` markers.

Source of truth is each binary's own `--contract` flag output (ctx-context, ctx-verify, ctx-scan, ctx-cage); the script builds all four with `cargo build -q` before invoking them, so a `--contract` change never goes stale relative to docs as long as this runs. It's invoked two ways: `--write` (default) rewrites the marked block in place in each doc; `--check` (used by ctx-verify's `contracts` battery check) emits `FAIL:` lines to stderr and sets exit code without modifying files. In `--write` mode, most errors (missing doc, missing markers, build failure) call `exit 1` directly rather than accumulating.

Block assembly order is fixed: ctx-context, ctx-verify, ctx-scan, ctx-cage, one `- **label** — text` line each. The `committed_block` awk extractor and the in-place rewrite awk both key off exact string match of the `$BEGIN`/`$END` marker lines — do not hand-edit text between markers or add a second occurrence of either marker in a doc, since the replace logic is not marker-count-aware beyond first BEGIN/END toggle. `BIN_DIR` is hardcoded to `target/debug`, so this assumes a debug build environment (no `--release` support).

Called by ctx-verify's `contracts` battery, meaning the four binaries' `--contract` string format is a de facto wire contract with this script — changing what `--contract` prints requires re-running `--write` or CI's `--check` fails.